CONTEXT
Here is a multiple-choice question in JSON format.
{
    "question": "Which of the following statements is true?",
    "choices": [
        {
            "choice": "Because strings, lists, dictionaries, and sets are all a type of Python sequence, they all support common sequence operations such as slicing.",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "All built-in data structures in Python share similar properties and functionalities, which means we can use them interchangeably.",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "Both lists and strings support positive and negative indexing.",
            "correct": "true"
        },
        {
            "choice": "A data structure is defined as a collection of data organized in a sequence where each element in the sequence has a different index number.",
            "correct": "false"
        }
    ]
}

Evaluate the above question based on the principles that are used to evaluate multiple-choice questions.
